  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">This letter deals with John Anderson Collins&apos;s salary and expense account. &quot;So disaffected was [James Sloan] Gibbons with my course, that I did not render my bill of expenses, which amounted to two hundred sixteen 14/100 dollars.&quot;</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">In the postscript, John Anderson Collins says: &quot;My wants are great---My necessities are pressing. Collins continues with these lines, which he writes in pencil: &quot;The Am[erican] Society owes me from 1000 to 1200$. The Mass. Society owes me about $475---I owe nearly 700$---I want only enough to pay my debts.&quot;</subfield>
  </datafield>
